Chicken Rice Divan Bake

1 packages (10 ounces each) frozen broccoli spears
1 cup grated Cheddar cheese
2 cups cubed cooked chicken
salt and pepper
1 cup cooked rice
2 tablespoons butter
2 tablespoons flour
1 cup milk
1 tablespoon lemon juice
1 cup sour cream
PREPARATION:

Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Arrange broccoli in 13x9x2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with half the cheese; top with cubed chicken. Season with salt and pepper; spoon on the cooked rice. 
In a saucepan, melt butter over low heat. Blend in flour; add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and bubbles. Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and fold in the sour cream. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes. 

Serves 4 to 6.
